      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You're absolutely right to notice that framing this as a \"debate\" often sidesteps the ethical consensus that access to care is a human right in many modern legal and moral frameworks. While critics cite efficiency concerns, many of those arguments prioritize maintaining existing privatized systems over addressing clear public health outcomes. Ultimately, viewing healthcare solely as a market failure misses the core ethical imperative that access to medical care is fundamental to human dignity and should not be treated as negotiable leverage.",
